3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Bitget calculates funding rates every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC using a time-weighted average of the premium/discount between the perpetual price and spot index. The funding rate is capped at ±2% per interval to prevent extreme payments. Traders holding positions at settlement times automatically pay or receive funding based on their position side and the rate sign. Bitget's index price aggregates spot prices from major exchanges including Binance, OKX, and Coinbase."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","BTC","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"BTC/USDT on Bitget attracts funding rate arbitrage due to its mega-volume status and the exchange's growing institutional adoption. The pair consistently ranks among the top 5 perpetual contracts by open interest on Bitget, ensuring tight spreads and minimal slippage for large positions. Bitcoin's status as the most liquid cryptocurrency pair provides predictable funding patterns and reduced basis risk compared to altcoin perpetuals."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Bitget's BTC/USDT funding rates typically range from -0.1% to +0.3% per 8-hour interval, with monthly averages fluctuating between 0.01% to 0.15%. During bull markets, positive funding dominates as long traders pay shorts, while bear markets see more frequent negative rates. Weekend periods often show lower absolute funding rates due to reduced trading activity. Bitget's relatively newer market presence means funding rates can be more volatile than established exchanges, creating enhanced arbitrage opportunities for experienced traders."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities and Strategies"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Cross-exchange arbitrage between Bitget and larger venues like Binance or OKX frequently yields 5-20 basis points per funding interval due to Bitget's growing but still developing liquidity pools. Delta-neutral strategies work effectively on Bitget by simultaneously holding spot BTC and short perpetual positions to capture positive funding. The exchange's copy trading ecosystem can amplify funding rate movements as retail traders follow popular strategies, creating predictable rate spikes. Bitget's fast listing of new Bitcoin derivatives provides early arbitrage opportunities before rates normalize with other exchanges."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations and Management"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Bitget's shorter operational history compared to established exchanges introduces counterparty risk that traders must factor into funding rate strategies. The exchange's customer support inconsistencies can create challenges during high-volatility periods when rapid position adjustments are needed. Limited institutional tools mean advanced risk management features available on older exchanges may not be present. Despite growing liquidity, sudden large withdrawals or technical issues could impact funding calculations, making position sizing and exit strategy planning crucial for funding rate arbitrageurs on Bitget."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often are funding rates paid on Bitget BTC/USDT perpetuals?","answer":"Funding rates are calculated and paid every 8 hours on Bitget at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC. You only pay or receive funding if you hold a position at these exact settlement times."},{"question":"What is the maximum funding rate for BTC/USDT on Bitget?","answer":"Bitget caps funding rates at ±2% per 8-hour interval for BTC/USDT perpetuals. This translates to a maximum of ±6% daily funding rate in extreme market conditions."},{"question":"Does Bitget charge additional fees for funding rate payments?","answer":"No, Bitget does not charge additional fees for funding rate payments. The funding amount is directly transferred between long and short position holders based on the calculated rate."},{"question":"How does Bitget calculate the BTC index price for funding rates?","answer":"Bitget's BTC index price aggregates spot prices from major exchanges including Binance, OKX, Coinbase, and Huobi using volume-weighted calculations. This index price is used to determine the premium/discount for funding rate calculations."}]}]
